snippet.textDisplay:
Hmm, the quickness at ending the word "breath" in the chorus just rubs me the wrong way for some reason. I am weird, I know. It is a novel idea doing it that way. If it were me, I would keep the preceding "breaths" short as they are, and then hold the note for the finals ones in each chorus.
Performance wise, I see this receiving a middle of the pack result. 13th-20th seems more than fair. I think the juries will like it, but the televoters will send their votes elsewhere.
My personal score: 6 out of 10
